Package mmj.gmff

Class GMFFExportParms

java.lang.Object
mmj.gmff.GMFFExportParms
All Implemented Interfaces:
Comparable<GMFFExportParms>
public class GMFFExportParms extends Object implements Comparable<GMFFExportParms>
GMFFExportParms holds the parameters from a single RunParm of the same name plus a File object for building relative paths.

It is basically just a data structure with some attached utility functions on the data elements.

During validation however, the GMFFFolders for the exportDirectory and modelsDirectory are instantiated and saved for later use.

The reason for creating this class is that GMFF parameter type RunParms are not validated and processed until GMFF is initialized, typically when the user requests an export. So the RunParms are cached until initialization time.

The GMFFExportParms are keyed by exportType.

  • Constructor Details

    • GMFFExportParms

      public GMFFExportParms(String exportType, String onoff, String typesetDefKeyword, String exportDirectory, String exportFileType, String modelsDirectory, String modelId, String charsetEncoding, String outputFileName)
      A constructor to build a GMFFExportParms object without validating any of the parameters.

      See mmj2\doc\GMFFDoc\GMFFRunParms.txt

      Parameters:
      exportType - Export Type (e.g. "html" or "althtml")
      onoff - OnOff ("ON" or "OFF")
      typesetDefKeyword - Metamath $t comment keyword (e.g. "htmldef" or "althtmldef")
      exportDirectory - where output files written
      exportFileType - File Type including the period (e.g. ".html")
      modelsDirectory - Directory where GMFF Models are stored for this Export Type
      modelId - Model Id for this GMFFExportParms instance.
      charsetEncoding - Charset Encoding Name (see doc).
      outputFileName - Output File Name minus the file type; if omitted file name composed using theorem label.

    • areExportParmsValid

      public boolean areExportParmsValid(File filePath, Messages messages)
      Validates Export Parms data.

      For ease of use, validation does not stop at the first error found. Any errors are accumulated in the Messages object.

      However, if onoff set to "OFF" the following parameters are not validated.

      Parameters:
      filePath - path for building directories. May be null, absolute or relative.
      messages - The Messages object.
      Returns:
      true if valid otherwise false.
